In fiscal year 2023, Siemens AG sold 3.5% of the shares in Siemens Energy AG that were held as pension assets at that time. This resulted in a gain of €213 million from the disposal of investments. As of the balance sheet date, Siemens AG directly held a 21.0% stake in Siemens Energy AG. A reversal of impairment in the amount of €166 million was made on these shares based on Xetra closing price on the balance sheet date. As of the reporting date, the carrying amount of the investment in Siemens Energy AG amounted to €2.1 billion.